<section id="itsm_id">
  <title>xml:id</title>

  <para>Identifier - the <code>id</code> attribute from the <code>http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/</code>
    namespace is used to identify a <olink targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/itsm_locQualityIssues.xml"
      targetptr="itsm_locQualityIssues"><code>&lt;locQualityIssues></code></olink> or <olink
      targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/itsm_provenanceRecords.xml" targetptr="itsm_provenanceRecords"
        ><code>&lt;provenanceRecords></code></olink> element.</para>

  <para><emphasis>Value description:</emphasis> xs:ID</para>

  <para><emphasis>Default value:</emphasis> undefined</para>

  <para><emphasis>Used in:</emphasis>
    <olink targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/itsm_locQualityIssues.xml"
      targetptr="itsm_locQualityIssues"><code>&lt;locQualityIssues></code></olink> and <olink
      targetdoc="../../elements/itsm/itsm_provenanceRecords.xml" targetptr="itsm_provenanceRecords"
        ><code>&lt;provenanceRecords></code></olink>.</para>
  <warning>
    <para>Since the ITS Module reuses the W3C namespace <code>http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its</code>
      it cannot use <code>xs:NMTOKEN</code> identifiers as the XLIFF Core or
      other Modules. Implementers need to be aware that <code>xs:ID</code>
      has to be globally unique.</para>
  </warning>


</section>
